added.title: The Guest
added.description: Vic & Val blame each other for eating all the food in the kitchen and making a huge mess! However, they soon discover that a ghost is actually to blame! They enlist the help of Achi to unlock the world of spirits among them and kick the ghost out of their house!

added.title: Ener-G-Shoes
added.description: When Vic uses trickery to buy a pair of super cool sneakers from Maria Teresa's yard sale, the shoes try to walk him to his demise as punishment.

added.title: La Cucarachita
added.description: When Vic's beloved pet cockroach dies, Vic turns to Charlene's dark magic to bring her back to life.

added.title: Lords of Ghost Town
added.description: When V&V recruit a ghost to scare away a bully, they end up messing with the realm of the dead, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: My Fair Achi
added.description: V&V enter Achi in a dog show competition to win a golden trophy, but their overbearing ways drive Achi to the edge.

added.title: Oddities
added.description: When a mysterious carnival barker fuses V&V together, they must find a way to come unstuck.

added.title: I……am Vampier
added.description: When Vic enters the Monte Macabre film festival, he gets insecure about his artistic vision and decides to copy the work of others, but ultimately learns that staying true to yourself is what's most important.

added.title: Victor the Predictor
added.description: When Victor becomes convinced he has a special talent as a psychic, he decides to use his new mental abilities to counsel those around him - until one piece of advice goes too far.

added.title: Kindred Spirits
added.description: When Val becomes friends with the ghost of a silent film star, their friendship turns out to have dire consequences.

added.title: Decoding Valentino
added.description: When Val goes on an adventure with Isabella to decode an ancient language, he has to come to terms with the fact that Isabella is smarter in order to save himself.

added.title: Journey to Maize Mountain Part 1
added.description: When Vic & Val destroy Monte Macabre's corn supply, they travel with Sal to Corn Mountain to replace it. But in order to get the corn, they have to shrink to the size of ants, creating all kinds of problems!

added.title: Journey to Maize Mountain Part 2
added.description: When Victor and Valentino destroy Monte Macabre's corn supply, they journey to Maíz Mountain with Sal to replace it. But in order to get the corn, they must shrink down to the size of ants and embark on a mythical adventure that they'll never forget!

added.title: Escaramuza
added.description: When Val's favorite Escaramuza team loses a member, he convinces Xochi to join the squad. He becomes her coach and will do anything to win the big competition.

added.title: Los Perdidos
added.description: When Vic joins a group of nighttime skaters called Los Perdidos, Val becomes suspicious of Vic's strange, new, vampire-like behavior.

added.title: Los Pajaros
added.description: When Valentino trades Huitzi's gifts for one of his own, the birds in town start to turn on him.

added.title: Get Your Sea Legs
added.description: When Victor gets teased for not being able to swim, he befriends a mermaid who offers to help, but at a cost.

added.title: Guillermo's Girlfriend
added.description: Vic & Val try to cheer up a heartbroken Guillermo by reuniting him with his lost love.

added.title: The Lonely Haunts Club 3: La Llorona
added.description: When Val sets out to get a little privacy in the woods, Vic is bent on pranking his unsuspecting brother,  that is, until Val goes missing.

added.title: Starry Night
added.description: When Vic and Val embark on a camping trip in the woods, their friends start to act suspicious and strange.

added.title: Fueygo Fest
added.description: When Vic and Val throw the biggest kid bash ever, they realize they aren't the party planners they thought they were as things start to fall apart.

added.title: Villainy In Monte Macabre
added.description: In a crossover episode with the show Villainous, V&V team up with Dr. Flug and Demencia to try to find a squid monster who is disguised as a human in Monte Macabre.

added.title: Folk Art Friends
added.description: When Vic and Val accidentally release some mischievous alebrije spirits, they must enlist the help of master mischief-maker HueHue to help catch them.

added.title: The Cupcake Man
added.description: When Victor's bad behavior gets out of control, Chata sends him to the one man in town who can set him straight, The Cupcake Man.

added.title: Charlene Mania
added.description: When Vic attempts to have the perfect day off, the town's sudden obsession for Charlene gets in his way.

added.title: Old Man Teo
added.description: When Vic and Val are tasked to volunteer at an Old Folks' Home, Val becomes buddies with the oldest, crankiest person in Monte Macabre and helps him reclaim his youthful power.

added.title: Poacher Patrol
added.description: When Don bestows Val the responsibility of patrolling the lake, Val takes it too far and stops who he believes to be a poacher -- with disastrous consequences.

added.title: In Your Own Skin
added.description: When Valentino is mocked for his lack of style, he's determined to get a designer hoodie to prove he has a sense of fashion, which turns out to be harder than it looks.

added.title: Ghosted
added.description: Vic makes a ghost friend but when she interferes with his shot at being part of the cool kids' Tlatchtli team, he must choose between the two.

added.title: Carmelita
added.description: Chata loans Xochi a car under the condition that Vic and Val can get rides when they need. However, the car becomes aggressive towards V&V and attacks!

added.title: Las Pesadillas
added.description: When Vic and Val experience a mysterious nightmare that turns deadly, they realize they must stop a sinister force from enchanting them to sleep forever.

added.title: Baby Pepito
added.description: When a mysterious "baby" appears on Chata's doorstep, V&V are convinced it's not what it seems.

added.title: Cenote Seekers
added.description: When Vic and Val are running too late to get a ride from Xochi to a fun water park cenote on a particularly hot day, they instead take their bikes. But they wind up lost in the desert and start to hallucinate while blaming each other for getting into this mess.

added.title: My Thirsty Little Monster
added.description: When Valentino discovers Victor has been hiding a baby vampire bat in the house, Victor must convince his brother that he can handle having a pet.

added.title: La Planchada
added.description: When Vic gets the chicken pox and is forbidden from playing in a tag tournament, he summons a mythical ghost nurse to cure him.

added.title: Tez Breaks Bread
added.description: When Tez returns to town and invites Chata and the boys to a dinner party, she insists they attend so Victor and Valentino set out to expose him as the evil magician he truly is.

added.title: Through the Nine Realms of Mictlan
added.description: When Victor and Valentino cause their ghost friend Cristina to miss her train to the 9th level of the Underworld, the boys now must guide her on a harrowing journey through the treacherous trials of the first 8 levels of the underworld to reunite Cristina with her family.

added.title: The Dark Room
added.description: After getting rejected by a photography club, Val tries to get a picture of the legendary Chupacabra in order to prove himself.

added.title: The Collector
added.description: When Vic accidentally loses one of Val's prized coins Val makes a deal with a mysterious antiques collector to replace it, but the deal has terrible consequences.

added.title: Boss For a Day
added.description: When Chata lets Vic be the boss of the taco stand for the day Vic decides to fire Val, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Cuddle Monster
added.description: After being told by Chata that they can't get a pet, Vic & Val adopt a wild lizard, unaware of its magical properties, and decide to keep it secret from Chata.

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val holds a grudge against Vic, unwittingly attracting an evil cadejo, a mythological wolf-like beast.

added.title: It Grows
added.description: As everyone celebrates Valentino for growing his first facial hair, a jealous Vic resorts to magical methods to grow a mustache and compete for attention.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 1
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: Welcome to the Underworld 2
added.description: After Victor loses a wrestling match, Victor and Valentino journey to the underworld to seek advice from their uncle, a famous wrestler named El Toro.

added.title: A New Don
added.description: When Vic & Val discover that Don isn't really himself, it's up to them to use his kooky codex of conspiracies to save him.

added.title: Churro Kings
added.description: When Vic & Val start making good money from selling churros at the taco stand, their lust for stuff makes them do dirty tricks to take out their competition.

added.title: Know It All
added.description: When Vic accidently unleashes evil bats from a cave, it's up to the boys and Don to protect the town, but Vic's know-it-all attitude keeps getting in the way.

added.title: Fistfull of Balloons
added.description: When Vic gets double-crossed during a water balloon fight, he goes on a revenge mission to find out who was responsible.

added.title: Love at First Bite
added.description: Val crushes on a girl named Matty, who Vic is suspicious of but Val ignores his warnings. When Val goes to dinner at her house she turns into a Matlazihua and he discovers he's what's for dinner!

added.title: Go With the Flow
added.description: When Sal stays with Vic & Val, the boys are annoyed by him as their roommate but eventually they learn how cool and magical he is.

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: When Vic finds an ancient relic that summons a gang of mischievous creatures, he uses them to do his bidding, which has disastrous consequences.

added.title: Guillermo's Gathering
added.description: When Vic & Val are forced to go to Guillermo's boring birthday party, they devise a scheme to leave early, but end up discovering that the party is way cooler than they thought.

added.title: Balloon Boys
added.description: Vic & Val go on a hot air balloon trip with Sal and compete to be his favorite, but things go awry when they try to use the magical Nazca Lines to their advantage.

added.title: Escape From Bebe Bay
added.description: When Vic & Val accidentally turn themselves and Don into babies, they must escape a daycare center in order to change back to their normal ages.

added.title: Band For Life
added.description: When Vic and Val tag along with Xochi to a punk concert, they want to prove that they're cool enough to hang out with her. But in a desperate attempt to be cool, they wind up destroying the concert.

added.title: Tez Says
added.description: Vic & Val are in awe of the new magician in town, but things go awry when they agree to help him out with a new trick - despite Chata's wishes.

added.title: Forever Ever
added.description: When Vic and Val do a sloppy job cleaning up in Maria Theresa's attic, they accidentally set off a time loop, trapping them in an endless series of chores forever! They must figure out how to stop the loop and return time back to normal.

added.title: Dance Reynaldo Dance
added.description: Vic is desperate to win the cash prize for the dance contest in Monte Macabre and is frustrated that his partner Val won't let him call all the shots. Instead he chooses a different partner: Reynaldo. But Vic pushes Reynaldo too hard to execute his artistic vision. Eventually he learns that in order to be a success, you have to be equal partners.

added.title: Tree Buds
added.description: Vic and Val build a treehouse and Val dismisses Vic with a frivolous task so he can build the treehouse exactly how he wants. But when Vic returns unknowingly with a branch from El Arbol Vampiro, Val's perfect treehouse turns into a nightmare!

added.title: The Lonely Haunts Club 2: Doll Island
added.description: In order to prove their bravery, V&V head to a haunted island to retrieve a special doll, but Charlene and Pineapple are intent on getting it first.

added.title: Cat-Pocalypse
added.description: When Vic gets sick and is stuck in his room, he spies on Pineapple and becomes convinced that Pineapple is creating an army of zombie cats. Val agrees and the two become obsessed with stopping Pineapple before it's too late!

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Victor sets up a haunted corn maze, but the town kids think it's lame. Vic decides to make the maze scarier by enlisting the help of El Silbon (The Whistler) to really scare the kids, but El Silbon has plans of his own.

added.title: On Nagual Hill
added.description: Vic & Val take over a forest hill and build an epic waterslide, disturbing the plants and animals that normally inhabit it. But when a Nagual (a human with the power to transform into animals) transforms Vic into a chicken and Val into a donkey, they learn to sympathize with the animals and understand the world a bit more.

added.title: El Huesped
added.description: iVic y Val se culpan el uno al otro por comer toda la comida de la cocina y hacer un gran lío! Pero pronto descubren que la culpa es de un fantasma. iAhora deben pedir la ayuda de Achi para librar al mundo de los espíritus que hay a su alrededor y echar al fantasma de su casa!

added.title: La Cucarachita
added.description: Cuando la amada cucaracha mascota de Vic muere, Vic recurre a la magia oscura de Charlene para devolverle la vida.

added.title: Achi el mejor
added.description: Victor y Valentio inscriben a Achi en una exhibición canina para ganar un trofeo dorado, pero su comportamiento autoritario desespera a Achi.

added.title: Energy Shoes
added.description: Cuando Vic usa engaños para comprar un par de zapatillas espectaculares de la venta de garaje de María Teresa, el calzado trata de llevarlo a su perdición como castigo.

added.title: Victor el Predictor
added.description: Cuando Víctor se convence de que tiene un talento especial como psíquico, decide usar sus nuevas habilidades mentales para aconsejar a los que lo rodean, hasta que un consejo va demasiado lejos.

added.title: El cuarto oscuro
added.description: Tras ser rechazado por un club de fotografía, Val intenta conseguir una foto del legendario Chupacabra para demostrar su valor.

added.title: El Coleccionista
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic pierde una de las preciadas monedas de Val, Val hace un trato con un misterioso coleccionista de antigüedades para reemplazarla, pero el trato tiene consecuencias terribles.

added.title: Victor y la Lechuza
added.description: Después de fingir una lesión para no tener que trabajar, Vic se gana la compasión de todos mientras que, sin saberlo, atrae la atención de una peligrosa criatura mítica.

added.title: Jefe por un dia
added.description: Cuando Chata deja que Vic sea el jefe del puesto de tacos por un día, él decide despedir a Val, lo que trae consecuencias desastrosas.

added.title: Nueva Mascota
added.description: Después de que Chata les dijera que no pueden tener una mascota, Vic y Val adoptan un lagarto salvaje, sin conocer sus propiedades mágicas, y deciden mantenerlo en secreto para que Chata no se entere.

added.title: Los Cadejos
added.description: Val le guarda rencor a Vic, lo cual atrae sin querer a un malvado cadejo, una bestia mitológica parecida a un lobo.

added.title: Crece
added.description: Mientras todo el mundo celebra a Valentino porque le creció su primer vello facial, Vic se pone celoso y recurre a métodos mágicos para dejarse crecer el bigote y competir por la atención.

added.title: Sale el Don
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val descubren que Don Jalapeño no es realmente él mismo, depende de ellos usar el alocado libro de conspiraciones de Don para salvarlo.

added.title: Los reyes de los Churros
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val comienzan a hacer dinero con la venta de churros en el puesto de tacos, su deseo por objetos los obliga a emplear trucos sucios para eliminar a la competencia.

added.title: Sabelotodo
added.description: Cuando Vic accidentalmente libera malvados murciélagos de una cueva, depende de los chicos y de Don proteger el pueblo, pero la actitud de sabelotodo de Vic pone en peligro la tarea.

added.title: Duelo de globos
added.description: Cuando Vic es traicionado durante una guerra de globos de agua, emprende una vengativa misión para descubrir al responsable.

added.title: Amor a primera mordida
added.description: A Val le gusta una chica llamada Matty, y Vic sospecha de ella, pero Val ignora sus advertencias. Cuando Val va a su casa a cenar, ella se convierte en una Matlazihua, iy Val descubre que él es la cena!

added.title: Sigue la corriente
added.description: Cuando Sal se queda en lo de Vic y Val, los chicos no lo soportan como compañero, pero finalmente descubren lo genial y mágico que es.

added.title: Aluxes
added.description: Vic encuentra una antigua reliquia que invoca a una pandilla de traviesas criaturas, iy las consecuencias son desastrosas!

added.title: La Fiesta de Guillermo
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val se ven forzados a ir a la aburrida fiesta de cumpleaños de Guillermo, crean un plan para irse temprano, pero terminan descubriendo que la fiesta es mucho mejor de lo que pensaban.

added.title: Ninos de Globo
added.description: Vic y Val salen de viaje en globo aerostático con Sal y compiten por ser su favorito, pero las cosas se complican cuando tratan de usar las mágicas líneas de Nazca a su favor.

added.title: El Gran Robo de Bongos
added.description: Los chicos olvidan conseguir un regalo para Chata en el Día de la Abuela y en un movimiento desesperado, le regalan los bongos que pidieron prestados a Xochi. Sabiendo que deben devolver los tambores, Victor y Valentino fingen ser ladrones para robar los instrumentos.

added.title: Escape de Bahia Bebe
added.description: Cuando, por accidente, Vic y Val se convierten a sí mismos y a Don en bebés, deben escapar de una guardería para poder volver a sus edades normales.

added.title: Banda de por Vida
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val acompañan a Xochi a un concierto punk, quieren demostrar que son lo suficientemente geniales para salir con ella. Pero en un intento desesperado por tener onda, terminan arruinando el concierto.

added.title: Tez dice
added.description: Vic y Val están impresionados con el nuevo mago de la ciudad, pero las cosas se complican cuando aceptan ayudarlo con un nuevo truco, a pesar de los deseos de Chata.

added.title: Eternamente
added.description: Cuando Vic y Val limpian el ático de María Teresa a medias, ipor accidente inician un bucle de tiempo que los atrapa en una serie interminable de tareas eternas! Ahora deben averiguar cómo detener el bucle y devolver el tiempo a la normalidad.

added.title: El Club de Los Solitarios 2, La Isla de las Munecas
added.description: Para probar su valentía, Victor y Valentino se dirigen a una isla embrujada para recuperar una muñeca especial, pero Charlene y Piña están decididos a obtenerla antes que ellos.

added.title: Gatocalipsis
added.description: Cuando Vic se enferma y debe reposar en su cuarto, espía a Piña y queda convencido de que está creando un ejército de gatos zombis. Val está de acuerdo con él y ambos se obsesionan con detener a Piña antes de que sea demasiado tarde.

added.title: Baila Reynaldo Baila
added.description: Vic está desesperado por ganar el premio en efectivo para el concurso de baile en Monte Macabro y está frustrado porque Val, su pareja, no le deja tomar todas las decisiones. Por eso, elige un compañero diferente: Reynaldo. Pero Vic presiona demasiado a Reynaldo para hacer realidad su visión artística. Al final, Vic aprende que, para tener éxito, hay que ser socios en igualdad de condiciones.

added.title: La Casa del Arbol
added.description: Vic y Val construyen una casa en el árbol, y Val se libra de Vic con una tarea sin importáncia para construir la casa exactamente como quiere. Pero cuando Vic regresa y trae, sin saberlo, una rama del Árbol Vampiro, la casa del árbol perfecta de Val se convierte en una pesadilla.

added.title: El Silbon
added.description: Víctor arma un laberinto de maíz embrujado, pero los chicos del pueblo creen que es muy malo. Vic decide hacer que el laberinto sea más aterrador con la ayuda de El Silbón para asustar de verdad a los chicos, pero El Silbón tiene sus propios planes.

added.title: En la colina Nahual
added.description: Vic y Val se apoderan de la colina de un bosque y construyen un tobogán de agua épico que perturba a las plantas y animales que solían habitar allí. Pero cuando un nahual (un humano con el poder de transformarse en animales) transforma a Vic en un pollo y a Val en un burro, ambos aprenden a empatizar con los animales y a entender el mundo un poco más.

added.title: La Planchada
added.description: Cuando Vic se enferma de varicela y le impiden jugar en un torneo de pega, convoca a una mítica enfermera fantasma para que lo cure.

added.title: Bienvenidos al Inframundo
added.description: Después de que Vic pierde una pelea de lucha libre, V&V viajan al inframundo para buscar el consejo de su tío, un famoso luchador llamado El Toro.
